annotationA: Procollagen lysyl hydroxylase (Plod) is a lysyl dehydrogenase with roles in Collagen IV biosynthesis. Plod localizes to the endoplasmic reticulum and is required for the secretion Collagen IV from haemocytes and fat body
annotationB: Glycosyltransferase 25 family member; Procollagen-lysine 5-dioxygenase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: lipopolysaccharide biosynthetic process
